name: Rahul Yadav
desc: Co-founder of Housing.com. He dropped out of IIT Bombay just months before completing his graduation

name: Ritesh Agarwal
desc: Founder and CEO of OYO Rooms. He dropped out of college at 17 to pursue his entrepreneurial dreams.

name: Kailash Katkar
desc: Founder and CEO of Quick Heal Technologies, a leading cybersecurity company. He dropped out after 10th grade and started his career repairing electronics.

name: Aadit Palicha
desc: Was supposed to get a Bachelor's Degree in Computer Science, but I decided to build Zepto instead

name: Gautam Adani
desc: Founder and Chairman of the Adani Group. He dropped out of his commerce degree in the second year to work in the diamond industry

name: Kunal Shah
desc: Founder of CRED and co-founder of Freecharge. He dropped out of his MBA program.

name: Jack Ma
desc: Co-founder of Alibaba Group. He started the e-commerce giant with 17 friends in his small apartment in Hangzhou, which served as their initial "workshop" and office.
